  "prompt": "What universities does Federal Signal recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Federal Signal may recruit new graduates from various universities, typically focusing on schools with strong engineering, business, and technology programs. While the specific universities they target can vary, they might prioritize institutions known for these disciplines. Common majors they may look for include:\n\n1. Mechanical Engineering\n2. Electrical Engineering\n3. Computer Science or Information Technology\n4. Business Administration or Management\n5. Finance\n6. Marketing\n7. Industrial Engineering\n\nTypically, companies like Federal Signal look for candidates from universities with strong engineering departments, such as:\n\n1. Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n2. Stanford University\n3. University of California, Berkeley\n4. Georgia Institute of Technology\n5. University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n6. Purdue University\n7. University of Michigan\n8. Carnegie Mellon University\n\nThese lists are not exhaustive and can vary depending on the company's specific needs, partnerships, and recruitment strategies. If you're considering employment with Federal Signal or similar companies, it\u2019s best to check their career pages or contact their HR departments directly for the most accurate information.",
